<br>
&quot;Plus, the exhaust gases left behind by those huge rockets <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>is</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> not very safe to breathe, either.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>are</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Power is dangerous. But the way to stop dangerous from becoming deadly is to be aware of the danger, and take steps to avoid that danger. This is also called risk mitigation. Since the Space Shuttle has flown well over a hundred times so far, we have had a LOT of practice in risk mitigation in this kind of a system.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>perhaps not the best example in light of recent events</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;To put it into perspective, all of the radioactive nuclides that were released by Chernobyl <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>was</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> also about 10 pounds worth.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>were</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Part 12.<br>
<br>
&quot;If we have a large<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&lt;&lt;&lt;,&gt;&gt;&gt;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> capable booster, the Solar System is easy to get to.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>remove comma</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Part 13.<br>
<br>
&quot;In this nuclear system, we have so much power to burn <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>than</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> we deliberately 'overshoot' on the way up, &quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>that?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Now, if you will remember, up above I mentioned that the exhaust of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>the</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> this nuclear spaceship...&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>remove</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;you can literally shoot the exhaust right <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>off</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the planet so fast that it never comes back.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>away from</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> replace<br>
