I have very very serious doubts. Each of the seven reactors is operating at 80,000 megawatts. The Phoebus 2B operated at  4000 MW. There is a huge radiation level (neutrons and gamma rays)around one of the engines, no less seven of them. Bringing all up to power and temperature at once is not <br>
